pageContext.claim: “African American youth unemployment has reached an all-time low in the history of our country.”
pageContext.analysis: African-American youth unemployment did hit a record low 15.7 percent in August 2019, but it has bumped up seven points since then. It was 22.5 percent in January. Plus, Trump says the youth unemployment rate was “through the roof” when he was running. There’s no question it was high, but it had already declined by more than half since the peak of the recession.
